caption: Great food
Happy this was close where I was staying and was open into late evening. Friendly staff & pretty good food.
Wasn't awful, but wasn't great. It's a Tex Mex Popeyes. Margaritia was good.
The food was terrible
We waited an hour for our food and then had to get our order to go. No avocados in avocado salad. No tortillas with fajitas. Very poor food all the way around.
Food very good ,service quality excellent. In lower level of Coach House hotel .

I typically stay away from restaurants attached to hotels, but Nole was a great find during a recent trip to New Orleans. Sade, our server, was so fantastic - great service and recommendations - she didn't steer us wrong.  We split the catfish beans and rice (oh my goodness!!!), the delicious queso, and some happy hour margaritas. The chips and salsa were also very tasty - hard to control ourselves until the food arrived. There are a few items that are the perfect creole/latin blend so get those instead of the typical latin fare you'd get somewhere else.

My Wife and I, spent the first few days in November in NOLA, and were staying at a hotel within a few steps of this place. They apparently hadn't been open very long (maybe a week?). Stopped in twice during our 4 day stay, and it would have been 3 times, had they been open Monday. The food was quite good and the service, even while very busy was very good. Great Bar staff( Say Hi to Willie, you can't miss him!LOL), and very pleasant servers. Even the G.M. was a nice guy! Should you be staying in the Garden District on St. Charles, Highly Recommended!!!

Derrick was our server and he was awesome and had positive vibes. The  biggest disappointment came from the change in ingredients, recipes and menu. I attended the grand opening of Nolè and everything was delicious. Idk why they would want to change😒 ANYTHING about the original menu. I'm saddened by this because I've been speaking so highly about the food here. The food was mostly bland. The chicken Fajitas taste like popeye's ( that's not a bad thing) I was excited about the fish Tacos (the ones from the grand opening was🎉 SPECTACULAR) but it was more like a Cabbage taco instead 😞THERE WAS SO MUCH CABBAGE 🤨🤨. The red beans and rice with catfish was lacking everything about it being a popular New Orleans dish(BLAND, BLAND, BLAND----🤔🤔 but how??? Popeye's red beans are better than the ones we ate here).  The queso and salsa was fresh and delicious. I gave 2 stars because the margaritas and queso was good.

After just wandering into Nolé restaurant we were greeted by lovely staff and enjoyed a really nice meal  great margaritas and awesome bread pudding. Our waiter David was very helpful and courteous. We will definitely be coming back.
Very cool vibe, but unfortunately the food and service don't match it.
Delicious food , attentive staff,  definitely a return visit!

One of the worst restaurant experiences I've ever had in New Orleans. Took several minutes to be seated for a party of 4 and there was hardly anyone in the restaurant. There was no bartender while we waited to be sat. I had to remind the hostess to seat us. Server was inattentive & forgetful. The food was bland and cold. Drinks on special were sickeningly sweet. We got our rice and beans and second round of drinks with the check...Will not be coming back here.
Shrimp & grits & the crab enchiladas! Small bites & Mexican menu. Great staff & good drink selection!
I was only in the outer bar area rather than in the restaurant. A great time with excellent Sazeracs and a fantastic server Matisse who I hope soon makes a trek to Paris.
Salsa was really good. Shrimp and grits were great and Willie begins the bar was fantastic!  Will certainly go back!

This place is really great. A little away from the French district, but all the better for it. We sat at the bar and had great service (and chat) with the barman, as well as the quality of food. Just what was needed!
It was pretty good,  but high priced for Mexican food and portions were small.

Not a great experience.  Our waitress was not the most pleasant.  The pitcher or house margaritas besides being tiny was not very good.  The chips and salsa was subpar.the chips were stallish, and the salsa just lacked flavor. The entree's were small for the price.  The enchiladas were the size of my middle finger and you get 3.  Not complaining about the size since most meals out are way too big but for the price not a good value.  The shrimp fajitas I had were cold and I didn't notice they still had the rails on.  But I will say the flavor was good.  The tamales my daughter and son in law had were aweful.  Could not eat them they were so salty.  The children's nachos and just chips with some cheese melted on top, and way too big of a portion.  Finally the nachos on the appetizer menu was tasty but cold. They looked smaller than the childs nachos. Then they added a 20% gratuity onto the bill.  I'm sorry to say this place won't last long unless major changes are made.  It looks like a nice fun place with a tasty menu.  We did complain about the tamales and the manager did comp them should have complained about the whole meal.  Not sure how this place has good reviews.
Love it like a fat kid does cake.
Delicious Mexican American cuisine and great happy hour. Go for the pitchers—sangria, mojito, margarita.
The drinks were good..but the food was so so.
Small portions but super satisfying! Will return.
A different twist on mexican food.
Great Food! Premiere Fusion of Latin American and Cajun. Great pricing and location on St. Charles Ave

Absolutely phenomenal lunch! Our server Whitney was GREAT! She really made the whole experience wonderful. Food and service was top notch. Sangria was quite possibly the best I’ve had. Get the Mac and cheese, you won’t regret it. Can’t wait to go back!

We came for fried chicken.  Turned out to be a chicken fajita plate for about $20. The veggies it came with were like coleslaw and kraut not a good combination and tortillas were tiny.   Happy hour pitcher of mohitos were barely enough for 3 people with way too much ice.  Black beans tasted soapy. Not happy will never come back.

If I could give them 0 stars I would.   We are visiting from out of town and Nole just canceled my reservation because they overbooked and had a private event scheduled.  I asked to come earlier or later and was completely turned down.  I just don't  understand why they only figured this out 2 hrs before we were due there for dinner. Bad planning on their part!! Unexcusable!
Very unique and delicious cuisine! Fried Chicken fajitas are amazing!
Very good service and I will have to get back to Nole' . Good came quickly and hot and we were tended to the full time.
Fantastic staff, fantastic food, fantastic location

It was alright mexican food. Not authentic taco truck or whole in the whole Mexican food like I like, but more of a High end Mexican food restaurant that tried hard but kinda miss the mark. The food lacked layers of flavor like real Mexican food. The drinks were decent, although the frozen blackberry margarita was almost the same price as my husbands brisket enchiladas. My husband also wasn't a fan of the brisket chunks versus shreds.. So 2 stars

Shout out to Jackson you’re The best even though you could not figure out how long my wife and I were married!The food  was great the drinks were great what can we say. We had an awesome time we had fun. thanks so much. The pork Stew was amazing. Not your typical cookie cutter Mexican fare.

It’s unfortunate that I have to write this review. I first came here for an event months ago and everything was good. Fast forward to my most recent visit, the food was awful and the service was even worse. The only reason for the 2 stars is because I really enjoyed my cucumber jalapeño margarita. The other guests didn’t like theirs and thought it was too sweet. Our server seriously was acting like he was high or something...he was really dingy and went missing at times. I ordered the chicken quesadillas...mushy, bland and terrible. We shared an order of queso. I liked it and ordered more but it never arrived. I confirmed with the server on two separate occasions and he said my order was in. He then went missing for about 30 minutes and I had to catch him to ask a 3rd time. He started talking in a fast, low and indecipherable voice. We all gathered that he didn’t put the order in. At that point, I told him to just forget it. Other than my margarita, the valet guys were the only other positive because they were very professional and speedy.
Brag brunch was a bust!!!

Called in from California to request something special for my friends. The first gal I spoke with was very helpful and polite. Called back and got the GM Adam(Hope I didn’t ruin the name)who was very efficient and accommodating. Great experience.  TLDR - Didn’t get to try the food but their customer service is 10/5!
Amazing!!

Nolé’s gluten sensitive menu and happy hour prices make for a very affordable meal in the garden district with pleasant open window seating. Kelsey was super friendly and helpful and went out of her way to ensure everything we received did not have gluten. Food was very tasty and exceeded our expectations.
We had brunch there.  The food and drinks were great! The staff was beyond great! Truly a wonderful experience. We will definitely return!
DELICIOUS food & drink!!  BlackBerry margarita is a must-have!

My wife and I came here for our 5 year Nolaversary, and we were not disappointed. Great pitcher of margaritas well worth the money. Food is well done blend of LA (the state, not the city) and Central/South American, good size portions at expected prices. Service was very good. Met the hype, and exceeded expectations for flavor/taste. Will be returning definitely.
Checks aren’t correct here either

In love with this place. They have great everything. The service is great, the food is great, the atmosphere is cool.  I know they are new and might still be figuring some stuff out but I insist on people giving them a chance.  Their brunch is pretty epic and so are the happy hour deals.
Margarita was terrible, service slow and food was forgettable.......
Drinks and food was extremely horrible... never will go again. ..

A wonderful experience! Delicious food and attentive service. Excellent combinations of mexican and NOLA flavors. Blackened chicken tacos with pineapple, queso dip with andouille and chorizo. Many more interesting things on the dinner menu. Looking forward to returning!

The food is good, authentic, and no where near as good as advertised.  The service is incredibly lacking. Whether it's the front or bar of house dropping that ball, it took 3 hours to serve an app, a drink, and an entree with a half full/empty house.  These issues need to be solved before giving this business serious thought.
This place is very nice and the drinks are very good

Cool concept and vibe with solid food, but we received the worst possible service. Came on a very slow Saturday afternoon and waited 35 minutes from ordering to get margaritas and almost an hour for a plain quesadilla. Thinking it may have just been a really bad waiter, but still hard to recommend it given the very poor quality service.
I had an incredible experience. The food was amazing, and so was all of the staff! Will definitely visit again and refer to friends and family! ❤

Just went here for lunch & waited 20min to be told Oh we take reservations 1st. The hostess did not say that when I walked in. All she said was I will seat you shortly. It's 20min & still no table. Then she tells me that they are low on servers. Very unprofessional & I will never come back. Now we wasted 30min of our Sunday for nothing!!!!

Not sure what the hype is about. It could be the brunch. Went for lunch. Low on servers but did not have a lot of tables. Food was okay. Higher expectations with higher prices. My server did not know the menu very well. Will consider giving it a second chance.
Used the Coolinary menu. Selection was great. Food and staff were excellent.

Everything was just, eh a ok, including the service. But, I went off the way up to four starts cause the fried chicken on the bone fajitas featured the BEST FRIED CHICKEN I have ever had! I didn't eat the tortillas, pico, or pretty much any of the meriad of sauces. I sure did wild down half a chicken! And I don't eat dark meat! This was the crunchiest, juiciest, best seasoned chicken ever! I can't say enough, so I'll stop right there!
Food and drinks were great. Service could use a little work. They should spend a little time picking up broken bottles and trash around the exterior.

edit: have to up to 5 stars now that I tried the fried chicken fajitas. One of the best dishes I’ve had in Nola. Also they made our margarita perfectly this time.  Decent food, okay Margs but a bit too sweet for me. The tacos were over-sauced. We were brought the wrong set of tacos and our waiter tried to make us keep them (lol). He also forgot to bring out our blue crab street corn, which was truly disappointing.  Lots of room to grow for this place. Will update my review once we visit again.
Great food
It was good, nothing to write home about. I was hoping for a little more New Orleans flavor to it.

Positive:  nice and professional staff. The environment is pretty and gives you a good feeling. Vallet parking is a treasure an that area. Nice outdoor seats.  Negative: we had to wait for all of our group of 11 to be seated.  the food has a lot of room to improve. The Avocado salad had a few chunks of avocado with very little taste. The "al's southern bone-in fried chicken fajitas" was basically fried chicken with some sides. Beef enchiladas had some fat chunks which two people who order it didn't finish the dish.
Night cap before heading to the room. St. Charles Coach House compliments of Choice Hotels. GETTING my points in....
Customer service was amazing! Molly was attentive and friendly. The food wasn’t that great. The empanadas didn’t have much flavor. The drinks were great.
Not all that..its a Mexican restaurant..expensive ..o
Great food & staff.
Great spot! Unexpectedly a good bargain, as well. Entrees and small plates, great happy hour, attentive staff, good drink. I will definitely be back.

Hardly anything we ordered (and we ordered quite a bit) was very good. We were a table of 7. The drinks were not great, the service was subpar. I have definitely had better Mexican food in 10 other NOLA places.
The appetizers were really good. The entrees were disappointing.   They don't allow you to mix and match tacos.  The fish sandwich didn't have enough fish so you had some in every bite.
Place does not have good food.

Lovely renovation of this restaurant. It looks completely different although it has the same owner. The menu is a unique twist on Mexican/Cajun fusion, no other menus in the city like it. The service was excellent and the food was delicious!
Great food !!!!!!!
The place was interesting.it had this artistic art..the food ofcourse was delicious

Homeowner Marty in New Orleans suggested this place. Very good, noe, really excellent. Nice ambiance. Quite large. Our waitress, Lorren was outstanding. As Marty indicated it was authentic Mejecano food plus New Orleans Cervaza

Tacos were not good the first time i went. 2nd time I ordered to go, just asked for soup. It took 30 minutes for the bartender to get soup which wasn’t  even hot.  Nothing was cooked in the tortilla soup.  Raw veggies, with literal chunks of corn on the cob in the soup. Never seen corn still on the cob in a soup.  It was dead in the restaurant so no reason it should have taken this long to put raw veggies in a cup w broth. When i asked about my food the bartender was rude, as if i was a nuisance to him. Total waste of $10. No way this place makes it. Awful food, awful service.
Great food fusions...not what you would expect..Awesome drinks and specials! Definitely returning to this spot.
Dinner was delicious, grilled salmon awesome
Very nice restaurant. Great food and service.
Large space, good guacamole
Good food, tasteful modern design, solid happy hour drink specials

The food was 5 stars. We loved the blue crab corn.  The only issue we had was that when we walked in, one of the hostesses spoke to the other hostess in an extremely rude and condescending way. So condescending in fact, that both my friend and I noticed and talked about it after we were seated. The conversation had something to do with reservations or something like that, but we were uncomfortable with the way that the hostess was being spoken to. She wasn't outwardly rude to us, but that doesn't excuse the way she spoke to her co-worker.  Otherwise, we found the service to be very good.

This place is an unknown gem,  but it won't be for long. Nolé is nice to look at from the outside,  inviting and cool. Inside,  the vibe continues.  The staff was friendly and seated me quickly. I opted to sit at the bar because it was quiet. I asked for a suggestion- guacamole or avacado salad.  The bartender said to go with the salad.  100% right.  The avacado salad was light,  fresh,  and super crisp with very fresh ingredients.  This is one of the best salads I've ever eaten. I followed that with chicken flautas- cheap and flavorful. I finished with the chicken tinga tacos and the carnitas tacos. They were both excellent. The service was great,  the staff was friendly. I loved this place and will be back.
Service and food were great.
MexTex with a creole style, was tasty, would have been better if what I ordered came to the table, but that was swiftly sorted out. I will be back.
Mothers Day Brunch. Fried Chicken was tasty....was expecting the Popeyes recipe...but a tad different.

Great experience. Upon arrival we were hesitant because my son wanted something specific. An employee, don't think she was the hostess answered all of our questions so we decided to stay. Our server (forgot name but biology major) was so sweet. Kept referring to my son (9) as "My love" and was just so friendly. If I had complain, I'd say my enchiladas were not piping hot, but they did come out very quickly. So many mirrors in the dining room was disorienting.
(Translated by Google) O9  (Original) O9

No Good , Never got my appetizers, after waiting more than an hour.  Food did not make since Food was cold I didn't get everything I asked for . Bad service , I got sick , my mother in law got sick .  Place was empty , and it still took a long time to get my food  They need to close restaurant down !!! Horrible
Good food...serene environment...real decent staff!
Excellent place to get Seafood cooked many different ways

In love with so many things about this restaurant.  The Nachos are delish..and can feed 4 people. A must have is the fired oyster taco and Al's Fried Chicken Fajitas. The prickly pear froze' and house margarita are so good! As for the designing of this space.. its so festive and comfortable.  I love the view of St. Charles Ave..

Chronically bad and unorganized service. The food faintly sparked with originality like adding red beans to nothing special quesadillas. I ordered the Side Car specialty drink. It was lukewarm. After joking that it should be warm resembling the heat from the motorcycle that pulled it along and there should be gnats in it to everyone's amusement, there was a gnat in it and another on the sugared rim. Our waitress had tables in the bar, to the far back right of the restaurant and another midway on the left. Who assigned that? The service was so slow we only ordered appetizers and our drinks came out ten minutes apart. We stayed about an hour and a half. The free valet parking was nice.
Amazing

Just had lunch here with a group of 10 others. Terrible service. The worst  100 bucks I've spent on "brunch" for my party of two in the last several years. Took 30 minutes to get our first round of drinks and not a single dinner plate was cleared. Time to shape up
This is an excellent place. Sangrias were great and the food was excellent and priced right!
Amazing food, great service, and such a fun ambiance. Trendy upscale dining meets a causal NOLA feel.
wonderful attentive staff, fabulous inventive foods - you will not be disappointed!!
For starters we had Chile verse chicken flautas and it was delicious. Our entrees were tres queso quesadilla and andouille and barbecue shrimp flatbread. We enjoyed it and have plans to return soon.
Great concept for a new restaurant! Everything I tried was very flavorful especially the blackberry margarita. It was very refreshing and delicious.  Cannot wait to go back 😃

Great food, restaurant, and staff. A very good value for dinner, but a little high for lunch [it's the same menu and portions for lunch and dinner]. Great job renovating the restaurant! Eric, the GM has a great F&B background and it shows. The lunch prices are the ONLY thing that kept me from giving 5 stars. As a concierge, I can recommend Nole with confidence to my guests.
This place is amazing! Atmosphere is amazing and the food was to die for! Would highly recommend this place!

Nolé was amazing!  The decor of the restaurant was super “posh”. The service, not only from the wait staff, but the owner and managers, was superb.  As a big group, we ordered almost every app and entree to share and every single dish was excellent. Can’t even pick my favorite cause they all were truly delicious.  To top it off the blackberry margarita was to die for!  Can’t wait to go back, SOON!!!
